snippet.textDisplay: It’s complicated and I’ll admit I don’t know everything. I wore masks on and off, mostly just at work because it was required. I was “sick” two or three times over the past year, nothing lasted more than 3 days and it was nothing more than a slight cough, runny nose, and general cold symptoms. We were around people with COVID and never got sick directly after. Tried to get tested but the clinics weren’t open 24 hours and my employer wouldn’t let us call off to get tested. So we couldn’t go. Many people got told they “probably” had it. Not tested. Many people I know who had it said it was nothing more than a cold for a couple days. All the way from toddlers to grown adults. I have one family member who is in icu with COVID now. Failing kidneys and medically induced coma. I really don’t understand the science behind how they classify symptoms when there’s such a huge disparity. I think there’s a lot of confusion with someone in dire straits having COVID and COVID causing there situations. Which is probably not usually the case. Idk, there’s a lot of questions I still have about the whole thing.
